<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Tournament Reports</td><form method='post' action=''><input type="hidden" name="PHPSESSID" value="71cd6057f09b34426d1aced53249d173" /><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Tournament Reports</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/treports/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/heroclix/treports/treports.php'>HeroClix</option><option value='/vs/treports/treports.php'>Marvel VS</option><option value='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magic/treports/treports.php'>Video Games and Movies</option><option value='/wars/treports/treports.php'>Wizards Minis</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> TORONTO TOC<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(5.00)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=12149'>Patrick "CaptCanada" Malboeuf</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=12149&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> April 21, 2003</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> Ah Toronto! Where it all started one year ago. Where I got my first big tournament victory, my first big tournament scandal, my first tournament report and with it a huge negative response, including Dom’s parody which would later make Yako insult me, my brother want to punch Dom in Atlanta and even later on be the basis for a friendship between me and Dom (how ironic).<br />
<br />
Toronto was also the start point of my most interesting enmity, the one with Josh Corwell Mott. Although you can read a good part of the story on my tournament report from last year, Dom’s parody is far more humoristic. But in order for anyone to appreciate this saga, here is a quick summary:<br />
<br />
--- Start of Saga ---<br />
<br />
Last year when I didn’t know anything about big tournaments one night I discovered GamePlayersNetwork and DGMA and was able to understand that the LOTR tournament experience went far beyond local tournaments (which I really liked attending due to high level of competition). So I go there and realize that if I ever want to play in big tournaments I need to win or to finish second at a TOC to make things easier.<br />
<br />
So out of the blue I decide to go to the Toronto TOC (cause it’s the only one I can go to) and I invite along my friend Merlin, who doesn’t know anything about the game. I propose to teach him to play on the way over Toronto and he accepts. Pat Sullivan also comes and that would be the very start of our road trip experiences.<br />
<br />
So we arrive at our hotel the day before, I teach Merlin how to play, we head to the church where the tournament is held, I throw up the Benedictine eggs I had for breakfast (it would become a ritual and somewhat of a running joke as I would continue to throw up before any tournament  and Pat would always take Bnedictine eggs and offer me some before a high level tournament) and we start the thing. It goes very well and Merlin is on fire, defeating everyone in his path reading his little rules booklet to remember the phases. So Merlin ends up playing Josh Cornwell Mott and tells him he just starting playing, so at one point Merlin plays thror’s map and says, I had to heal first and Josh says he won’t let him and wins because of that. Learning about that, the local players that Pat and I were become really upset about this way to play and decide we will argue with the judge that this is uncool. That is when we learn that LOTR has nothing to do with being cool and that what Josh did was perfectly legal. So I get frustrated and I decide to go on a crusade to meet Josh in the finals to kick his hiney to avenge Merlin. All works well except that gosh darnit Merlin keeps winning and during his last game I beat Josh and it becomes obvious that if Merlin wins his game, he will still be in the finals against Josh and will loose cause he’s clearly intimidated. So I tell Merlin the situation and he forfeits, allowing me to go to the finals with Josh, where I proceed to beat him hard, using the psychological advantage in an unusually mean way.<br />
<br />
So all is well, Merlin is avenged, I got my bye and my binder but then I proceed to tell this incredible story on GamePlayersNetwork and to my big surprise (being the new player I was) people don’t like the way I acted and all of a sudden I’m the bad sportsman. So I defend myself to no avail and I finally learn about the tournament rules forbidding collusion and the ones allowing someone to refuse take backs. A few days later I receive an email from Dan Bojanowski who very professionally says my bye will be taken away from me for collusion with Merlin and I tell him I accept this decision. That would be a huge lesson for me as I would learn the tournament rules by heart and would never let a sportsmanship issue to have an influence in my gaming at the high level of competition.<br />
<br />
Me and Josh would later meet at round two of the world championships last year, him playing Nazguls with 4 too great and terrible and me playing a trust me deck and I would proceed to win 2 successive games to advance in what remains 2 of the toughest games I have ever played. In the second game, Josh was moving to  site 9 with 1 boromir (one wound) and frodo with sting and I played Lurtz and a warrior. So of course he tries to make me miss my maneuver by saying “assignment” but I tell him Lurtz is fierce and he takes one archery so bormir takes Lurtz, frodo the warrior and then Lutrz comes fierce so he says fierce assignment and I say yes with Lurtz in front of Frodo and he says “you didn’t assign Lurtz to Frodo so Lurtz is left unassigned and Frodo survives” of course Enrique tells him that’s not the way things work and I advance to play Brochu in the semi-finals in a match completely lacking any psychological element, a real game between friends (with thousands of dollars at stake, although to this day Brochu keeps teasing me on the fact that he’s won like 27 000 US dollars on one shot and that doing well in Vegas got me 75 $…).<br />
<br />
So after Josh had said on his decktech page that he deserved to be on the fantasy team list cause he was 8th in the world and that my brother being mentioned was a joke and after calling Doug Faust a douche bag for forgetting him, Josh wrote me an email asking me what I was going to play at the Toronto TOC.<br />
<br />
--- End of Saga ---<br />
<br />
So with that Josh story, the fact that my brother, Pat Sullivan and his friend Steve were coming to Toronto in one of our road trips, I was expecting things to be pretty exciting, I was also looking forward to meet the guys at Nexus X and some of the players I had met from last year. I also told my brother about the little Dagliesh dwarves and he had big expectations.<br />
<br />
This year however we decided to drive to Toronto in the morning so we had to wake up at 4:30 and Pat went to pick us up ad 5:30. After picking up Steve we headed to Toronto with me on the verge of throwing up (with 1h30 of sleep from last night) and my brother sleeping like a baby.<br />
<br />
When we finally arrived to Toronto a cop standing in the middle of the road signals to Pat to pull over but Pat keeps driving until he realizes that he wasn’t one of those school guys with a stop sign but that Pat had been speeding and that he was that close to creating a cop pursuit. So he finally pulls over and backs his car all the way back to the cop who is apparently not pleased at the fact that Pat almost killed him by not stopping. But Pat being Pat he tells the cop his wallet is in his trunk and a few minutes later we hear laughter from behind the car and Pat comes back saying he went from a 175$ contravention with 3 demerit points to a 40$ contravention. I reiterate my belief that the UN should send Pat to the middle east and we would have people hugging and cheering in 1 week. Pat tells us that the British cop told him he was “ a good lad”.<br />
<br />
So we finally arrive at Nexus X and learn that the tournament started at 12:00 and not 13:00 but since Pat is the one who organized our trip, he planned to arrive one hour early just in case and we arrive in time to enter the TOC.<br />
<br />
There we meet Pierre Francois and his friend Steve from Laval who brought their standard decks instead of open and who are a little pessimistic about their chances in the wrong gaming environment. We also see Josh who only came with one of the Dagliesh dwarves, which is sad since my brother won’t get to see the two brothers in action.<br />
<br />
So with like 1:30 hours of sleep in the last 2 days I keep spiting, waiting to throw up but I took the precaution not to eat anything (gotta learn form experience) so I just walk around outside spitting waiting for the tournament to start. 24 players, 6 rounds, a two out of three final confrontation.<br />
<br />
I’m playing a bad beef fellowship with ents instead of men and lots of elves and hobbits with more stealths than usual since the horn is gone. I still play 4 foul creations but I use 3 galadriel lady of light in order to play elven companions for free which can be hugged before a double move. Anyways, it’s basically my brother’s bad beef post grima except I kept aragorn ranger of the north cause he’s a beast and by far the most unbalanced companion if you ask me. My shadow is a Gabor Vida shadow (the Hungarian inventor of the moria/isengard shadow) with the palanthir and all except that I changed a forger for a grima wormtongue just to be nasty and cause he’s an isengard minion and I can still trigger or play the palanthir with him. I don’t think I’m going to post this deck since it has been posted several times with variations but if some people really want the deck list just say so in the comment section.<br />
<br />
Round 1:<br />
<br />
Stephany<br />
<br />
Bad Beef/Vida v.s. Old skool fellowship with Moria<br />
<br />
She was starting Legolas and Arwen with Aragorn King in Exile and played aragorn’s bow, asphaloth, gwemegil, tale of gil galaad, etc. so as to go to 5 companions and to manage like 6 directed archery at site 5. Unfortunately for her isengard warriors have the tendency to make directed archery worthless, and all the pool she gave me allowed me to put all her cards in top of her draw deck.<br />
<br />
FW: 3<br />
<br />
Props: Stephany was nice and wore a Maple Leafs shirt which I completely approve, they are by far the coolest team to watch and are lead by Eddie the Goalie, my all time favourite goaltender. However if you ask me my pick is Anaheim cause Giguère is on fire and cause I went to goaltending hockey school with him and Jocelyn Thibeault.<br />
<br />
Slops: My brother beat me and managed to end his first game a few moments before mine. gosh darnit him.<br />
<br />
Round 2:<br />
<br />
Bad Beef / Vida v.s. Ranger/Elves Horn deck starting four disposable hobbits in order to start (kind of Jonh Kotek’s day 1 Las Vegas deck) with Moria.<br />
<br />
He bids 7 and starts, goes for Aragorn and plays legolas which is 6 companions. I play 2 enqueas and 3 nerteas so I’m quite happy with that and I draw one at site 2 so I damage legolas twice and kill exhausted Sam, kind of a long term investment since Frodo has 3 burdens now and cause I play palanthir chamber. He decides to move again and sacrifice the hobbits to make some room for other more important companions. I move to 2 and stop cause that’s what I’m supposed to do. But he plays Elrond and foul creation which really really sucks cause that means I won’t be able to do nothing on site 4 when I could have easily killed him so I only play some minions and he stops and proceeds to heal legolas with elrond herald to gil galaad. 5 directed archery with one healing each turn, this game is going to be long… So I move to 3 and stop. I manage to prepare another warrior combo and prepare for the kill but he draws another foul creation. gosh darnit. So he moves to 5 with my site which creates one more free peoples’ archery so I play everthing in order to try to stack some minions on swarm (and to oblige him to direct archery instead of only playing a few guys and loosing them to 3 undirected archery). But he plays secret sentinels cause I kept my pool for guard commander instead of palanthir so I loose swarm and armory which means my swarm does nothing making him exert some archers. Fortunately for me he forgets Elrond which means legolas is exhausted. I move to 4 and stop but I know I’m going to have to put some pressure on him or else he’s going to win very easily. I decide to stop for now and keep my 5-7, 7-9 option open in order for him to have less reconciliations before he moves to the sanctuary. So he moves to 6 and I can’t overwhelm him cause he’s got sting and the blue ring but I do play minions in order to put one against exhausted Legolas which means he dies. Good, but I have played too much minions until now, I count my minions and realise I will have to be careful. So I move to 5 and stop, his moria is doing nothing thanks to one grown suddenly tall and to my frodo son of drogo with pan and merry learned guide with treebeard combo: exert frodo to kill an orc, discard merry on treebeard, play a fresh merry and heal frodo from his wounds, and to that again and again and again which means 4 3 cards totally immune you against moria except for site 7 cavern entrance.<br />
<br />
So he plays boromir and moves to 7 and I don’t’ have enough minions to I only play conditions an Enquea which makes him stop. That’s when the TD announces there’s 10 minutes left to the game. So I proceed to move to 6 and then double to 7 and we both play very fast in order to avoid the time win or loss so on my double move to 7 I assign a 11 strenght minion to Frodo and exert with pan killing him but he forgets we’re at the cavern entrance (don’t worry I had Sam, gotta try it since the minion was Guard commander and since there was like a billion left in the pool). So my fellowship is unstoppable. That means he’ll have to double move to 9 so I quickly reoncile and he moves to 8 and I play 2 conditions and reconcile again so he’s got to make the decision before time is up. So of course he decides to move again (he had played horn on boromir and had aragorn with bow, rumil without a wound and elrond). So because the game goes to time a lot of people are watching and I must say things are not looking well for me cause I only got like 5 minions in hand. One good thing is I have relics out so I start playing some little minions and their scimitars but keep top decking free-peoples cards until I finally get my last nertea. So I play nertea and because he’s got 5 companions I can fetch the warrior that goes with the other warrior already on the table. So that’s 7 minions to his 5 companions but he’s got the horn and 3 of my minions are not moria orcs which means my guard commander is useless. He’s got the blue ring and sting which means I need 7 to overwhelm him. So that is when my killing Sam at the start of the game becomes crucial, I remove 2 burdens to get another minion and use the palanthir to put cards on top of his deck. His 5 first cards are shadow cards and then the sixth one is a god Orc Bane (he’s got no wound whatsoever on Frodo). The crowd unleashes a huge “ouch” as 8 minionshimmer the table and as the two isengard minions that go on frodo total exactly 14 strenght to overwhelm 7 strenght frodo. Can you say close game? Boy was that one tough.<br />
<br />
FW: 6<br />
<br />
Props: Despite what people might say, the Palanthir is not a useless card.<br />
Slops: At the end of the game I learned that because Josh had been playing Moria for the past month and winning with it that gaming community was made of like 75% moria shadow and 90% anti-moria fellowships. You could see 2 or even 3 orc banes everywhere with 2 or 3 stings with horns and lots of archery and even foul creations designed to get rid of warriors. Clearly I saw easier places to play moria.<br />
<br />
Round 3:<br />
<br />
Walter<br />
<br />
Bad Beef/ Vida V.S. Help in doubt and need with lots of companions.<br />
<br />
So he starts, has a really good draw since he gets aragorn with site, theoden with symbelmyne, plays eowyn’s sword and herugrim and gives me a ton of pool. I play swarms, a runner and guard commander and proceed to stack both, which is always a nice way to start a game. He moves again and says ouch to golden hall. On my turn I single move to 2. He moves to 4 with 7 companions ( I think there was like Alcarin and another no name rohan guy in there) so I play Enquea but he plays defend it and hope which means I can’t kill eowyn lady of rohan. I don’t play my stacked minions since he’s got help in doubt and need and a lot of ways to make his companions win. I move to 3. He moves to 5 with his 7 companions. Nertea, get enquea, get warrior to put with forger, play guard commander and a couple of minions and even get grima to bounce back his argorn’s bow, sword and horse. Palanthir gets rid of cards in hand and there’s like 5 minions on frodo.<br />
<br />
FW: 9<br />
<br />
Props: As much as my last game was close, there was no way Walter could have won that one.<br />
Slops: There was one more round before the lunch break and my entire body was yelling “BREAK”.<br />
<br />
Round 4<br />
<br />
Mike<br />
<br />
Bad Beef Vida/ almost the exact same deck of my round two opponent.<br />
<br />
I had met mike last year at the Toronto TOC and had played him in what is now known as the Guinness record for most mistakes in one game. A really cool guy which I had recognized and with whom I had talked a little. Seeing his 4 hobbits made me remember my second round and I really didn’t want that to happen again.<br />
<br />
So he starts bidding 5 which means that with pippin and sam he goes down to 1. He moves to 2, no enquea, he moves to 3 and intentionnaly kills one of his companions after loosing sting to golden hall but he calls golden hall which means he’s got more than one sting (to go with his more than one orc banes…). I move to 2. He moves to 4 with rumil but has to use him to foul creation me (gosh darnit it… once again a game that could have ended right there is allowed to go on…) so he stops. I move to 3. He moves to 5 without foul creation and I got the isengard combo but now it’s the pool that is lacking, I have no armory and only scavengers with no scimitar in discard pile and those two warriors and guard commander cost a lot so believe it or not my moria is choked by a ranger elf deck with absolutely no choking which is quite lame. But if I play nothing he’s going to move again to 6 quite easily and I don’t want to do that so I count the pool carefully and realise that with his 7 streght frodo (blue ring, sting and helm’s gate that he pathfindered) I can put one 7 strenght minion on frodo which means 3 wounds (thanks white mountains) with 2 warriors in play. At the very worst he’ll put the ring and go to 2 burdens which is a long term investment). So he resolves the skirmishes and takes one on frodo and then realises that it’s going to hurt. I exert the 2 warriors so that his entire party is exhausted. God I like those little buggers, they have like a billion uses. So I move to 4 and stay. He moves to 6 and I play guard commander with a couple of moria orcs, he obliged to assign to of them to exhausted companions which means legolas and argorn die (he assigned exhausted guard commander to faramir with last alliance to kill him but I sacrificed an armory to pump runner against gorn to kill him. So he’s down to 3 companions. I move to 4. Again, I have played a lot of minions and there aint that much orcs in my draw pile. I draw an awful hand, only getting 4 minions, including forger, grima and nertea which means that I won’t have enough pool to use the palanthir but clearly I have to take the risk so I play my 4 minions against his 3 companions (you know your draws are bad when you can’t play more than 4 minions and you’re playing a swarm deck) and forger and grima go on 5 strenght frodo (thank you blue ring) and he’s got no orc bane and that is game.<br />
<br />
FW:12<br />
<br />
Props: Great guy, great game, very close again.<br />
Slops: Trying to overwhelm frodo with everything but good old moria orcs, I’ve been struggling all day to draw into good minions and I have to find ways to overwhelm people with grima and nertea with less than 5 companions…<br />
<br />
Lunch Break. We go to a little place and I order a chicken sandwich, I eat half of it cause I’m going to throw up and I literally sleep on the table. And I keep spiting everywhere on the streets.<br />
<br />
Round 5:<br />
<br />
Josh Cornwell Mott!<br />
<br />
Bad Beef/ Vida v.s. … Bad Beef/ Vida<br />
<br />
Him and Malcolm have designed their version of my deck but have included saruman black traitor twice and put more stuff on frodo.<br />
<br />
From the start I knew this game was going to be an interesting one since I have never played a game with Josh without something crazy happening. The suspense was great since we were the only two undefeated players of the tournament (Pat and my brother had one loss) and since the rivalry that had begun at the Toronto TOC last year was allowed to continue. A new page in the sage would be written.<br />
<br />
From the start, before the game even begins Josh tells me: the time will start when I will be done shuffling, pointing at his own little timer. Apparently Josh doesn’t care about the fact that the official time has begun and that the judge has said we could start playing. So I look at him waiting for him to finish shuffling and he says, could you shuffle your deck more and since I judge I already shuffled it enough I answer: “yeah, I could, but I won’t”. So Josh is a bit confused and says, well I will keep shuffling until you shuffle your deck and we won’t play, so I say “that’s ok, we’ll just talk”. So Josh seems a bit confused and keeps shuffling his deck (I think his cards are now burning) so I call the judge and tell him: Josh feels I haven’t shuffled my deck sufficiently, could you shuffle it to his liking please and the judge proceeds to shuffle while Josh keeps shuffling and shuffling. So finally Josh is satisfied and we bid, I bid 0 cause I know he’s going to make me start and I don’t want to arrive at the palanthir chamber with burdens and he bids 4 to let me go first. I have a decent draw, I single move to 2 without any history. He does the same. I single to 3, really not in a hurry to get to cavern entrance. He singles to 3 as well. I single to 4, still stacking my companions in my hand in order not to go to 6 cause he’s stacking his Enqueas and Nerteas. Our 2 strategies are very different. He plays all his minions each turn, but I keep playing 0 or 1 minion and keeping all my other minions in my hand so that if he decides to double I kill him. Since we move so slowly we have plenty of time to prepare our fellowship and draw our stealths but when Josh moves to 5 I finally have enough pool to play minions and use the palanthir. Since he has transferred his frying pan to pippin to play sting on frodo, I could overwhelm him if I succeed in getting his stealth back on top of his draw deck. Only problem is I don’t have enough pool to play both enough companions to put 3 on frodo (was is needed to overwhelm him) and to put all of his 6 cards on top of his library. So in the end there’s 7 minions to his 5 companions and 3 left in the pool. So I put back: shadow card, shadow card and “swiftly and softly”. Yeah! So with enough luck he’s dead so I put the remaining minions on frodo. He resolves all the other ones first so I begin thinking maybe this is it but since Josh is a good player he had another stealth in hand (playing with the palanthir and not enough pool is like gambling and I’m not that good of a gambler). So at that point Josh calls JUDGE! Out of the blue and the judge comes to see him once again (as Josh has called the judge repetitively today). I look around me trying to figure out what I did wrong and waiting to see what he’ll find this time and he astonishes us all when he says: “could you look at the cards, I gotta go to the bathroom”. In the middle of a very close game, Josh decides he wants to go to the bathroom. I myself had to go madly since I drunk lots of water before the game and was dancing on my chair but he actually decided he would go now. So he leaves and I look at the judged, amazed and I tell him: “that Josh has some privileges as I can see” and he looks at me and smiles. So I tell him I gotta go to since I really needed to go and I wait for Josh to come out. When Josh finally comes out, another guy passes right in front of me, goes into the bathroom and closes the door, so I have to wait and when he finally comes out, I go in and smile a little since I’m crapping in the middle of the most important game of the Toronto TOC, unexpected break. So I come back fresh as a rose and we continue the game. Josh tells me we don’t have to worry about “their” time, on his timer we have still 15 minutes to play. So I move to 6, and he moves to 6 and then the judge calls TIME and Josh continues playing and so do I but when it’s finally my turn and I move to cavern entrance the judge comes to our table and he says, time has been called 5 minutes ago, why are you still playing. Josh answers: “well on my timer we still have time” and the judge finds a really nice way to put it: “tell me Josh why you think you have the right to make everyone in this room wait for you to finish your game when the time limit is made especially for everyone to have a fair an equal amount of time to play?”. So that’s it, we don’t have to play anymore, I get a timed win since time was called when we were both at six and I have 0 burdens and he’s got 4. Josh is furious and tells me, let’s keep playing so as I take my cards back and walk away, he keeps counting imaginary pool, anticipating how much I would have given him and playing minions with nertea and others, telling me: “ I would have beaten you”. So everyone had finished their game a while ago and where wondering what was happening and when I told Pat I had a timed win because Josh wanted to go to the bathroom, we all had a good laugh.<br />
<br />
Like I said, can’t expect to play against Josh without something crazy happening. He told me he would write to Decipher since he clearly deserved to win this game but all I could so was smile and try to remember exactly what had happened in order to update the Josh Saga.<br />
<br />
FW: 15<br />
<br />
Props: Josh the rules monger got screwed at his own game. Evil has been vanquished once again and peace has been re established at Nexus X. : )<br />
<br />
Slops: Boy oh boy I can already see all the negative critiques that will fill the comments section.<br />
<br />
Round 6:<br />
<br />
Patttttttttttttttttttttttttttttt!!!!!!!!!!!!! Sullivan<br />
<br />
Bad Beef/ Vida v.s. Mister Jones<br />
<br />
So Pat and my brother have only one loss and because I have a timed win, I am not sure of making the finals since the winner of me and Pat will meet the winner of my brother and Alex, an ex star wars player. So immediately me and Pat start to laugh and of course this game is going to be a lot different than the last one.<br />
<br />
Pat is playing basically Ryan Jones’ winning Vegas deck with modifications that Ryan helped him make, hence the title of his deck. He’s been doing quite well with it, only loosing once and I know that dunlend are tough on my free-peoples side.<br />
<br />
So Pat bids 1 to my 0 and lets me go first. Immediately he tells me: “I have to go to the bathroom” . We laugh a little and I move to 2, he plays a guy that kills allies and gets rid of galadriel right off the bat. I stop. He moves to 2 and doesn’t draw aragorn or faramir but does draw bill and a talent for not being seen early. He stops there. I move to 3 giving him lots of pool with only frodo, gandalf and pippin, he plays 3 dunlendings, one of which takes sites and the other one who stacks on sites. I assign those two on frodo and pippin, and the anti ally one on gandalf. Stealth, stealth. He had 2 war clubs on those two guys and thus I keep my frying pan on frodo. Yeah! He moves to 3 and stops, still not drawing a 4th companion. I move to 4 and stop when he plays Saruman with one guy, I kill pippin since he would have overwhelmed anyone else. He moves to 4 with 3 guys, but he has got 1 no stranger, 1 bill and 1 talent which means he gives me 3 twilight. Are you kidding? There’s no way I can kill him with 3 twilight, especially with Merry with escape but U do play a bunch of guys and he exerts merry to prevent boromir form being overwhelmed, no goblin swarms. I move to 5 and he plays a bunch of guys, including wulf which means he takes a site and is thus able to kill my gandalf with a pump on wulf’s fierce skirmish. He moves to after playing aragorn but uses sting to remove pool which means I am still choked like crazy and there is no way I can go near killing him, he has also played 2 betrayal of isengard which means that my 2 armories are useless. I have a bunch of moria conditions, including swarms but he manages to win all of his skirmishes and stops. I move to 6 with frodo, legolas, aragorn and merry and I use merry to discard him in another skirmish to prevent more sites from being taken. He moves to 6 and stops. I play haldir, get merry back from the tree, moving to 7 with 6 companions and he plays a bunch of minions and takes control of 2 sites but since we’re at causeway, in regroup I exert haldir twice, once with legolas and once with elrond to liberate 2 sites! Mad Tech! I mean, honestly, when has that happened in open format? So Haldir is exhausted, legolas has one wound, merry is discarded after taking archery wounds from the site and aragorn has one wound (and I still got my frying pan despite Pat playing 4 war clubs!). So he moves to 7 as well, knowing he’ll have no trouble double moving 7-9 but not letting me reconcile one more time before I attempt my own double move. So I have a good draw, + the severed his bonds that I have been stacking in my hand since site 5. I draw Lindenroot, sam and merry on the tree but I don’t want to play 6 companions since if he has his enquea that will kill my chances of double moving. So I only play sam and now have frodo, legolas, haldir, gorn and sam proper poet. I move to 8 and he plays 3 guys, one of which is Wulf and one of which takes sites and has a war club. Looks bad, but Treebeard comes to the rescue and wins against the tribe with war club (I keep my pan!), another dunlending exhausts legolas and haldir bits the dust against wulf. Fierce Wulf with club damages treebeard. I loose my frying pan, finally. So I got exhausted legolas, argorn with 1 wound, sam and frodo (and filibert!) So I move, he’s got constantly treathening on the table and has to use it since he doesn’t have much more minions in his draw deck, but anyway you look at it, gorn will take 3 guys, sam will take 2 and legolas one, and even frodo can take someone with ring and even survive if there’s a boost thanks to my stacked severed his bonds so pat plays what he can and assigns an anti-ally guy to filibert but that is not enough, frodo survives.<br />
<br />
FW: 18<br />
<br />
Props: Crazy game, we kept making jokes. Me deciding to put aragorn roth after all despite grima cc won me that game.<br />
Slops: Having to beat Pat and take away his chances of going to the finals in order for me to go to the finals.<br />
<br />
My brother lost to Alex which means the very expected Bad Beef final won’t happen. We take a break and head back inside to play the 2 out of three final.<br />
<br />
Finals<br />
<br />
Game 1:<br />
<br />
Bad Beef/ Vida v.s. Help in doubt and need with lots of no name rohan and gondor guys and lots of possessions.<br />
<br />
We sit down, Alex is an ex star wars players and seems nice. He bids 1 to my 0 and wants to go first. He plays gorn and another companion so he’s at 5, plays aragorn’s bow and moves to 2 easily. I cycle, playing a forger with palanthir and an armory and he moves to 3 loosing the bow, I put his cards back on top of his draw deck just so he doesn’t discard one shadow card to reconcile. I move to 2 and cycle. He moves to 2 with 5 companions giving me lots of pool after playing help in doubt and need. I play 6 minions to his 5 companions, and palanthir 3 of his 5 cards. 2 minions go on frodo, game.<br />
<br />
Game 2:<br />
<br />
I bid 1 to his 0 and I make him go first. He moves to 2 again with 5 companions, again I play armory and palanthir and put some cards back on top of hs draw deck, just to see what he’s playing, he moves again to 3 with rohirim shield and armor but those stay cause they are not weapons. I move to 2 and cycle. He plays gorn’s bow, rohirim bow and help in doubt and need and seems relieved. He moves to 4, I play 6 minions to his 5 companions, 2 of which are warrior and forger and I put back all his cards except one on top of draw deck. 2 minions go on frodo, game.<br />
<br />
My deck was a bad matchup for him, which lead to the fastest untimed two out of 3 final I have ever heard of.<br />
<br />
So I get the bye for worlds and continentals like I wanted (cause I want to play all 3 days at Origins) and Josh, Pat and my bro finish 4-2, Pat taking 3rd place and my brother taking 7th.<br />
<br />
We’re tired like crazy and want to head back to Montreal cause it’s a 5 hours drive but Pat keeps talking to people and to 2 girls in particular. At one point my brother stands in front of him and says: “ok Pat you’ve made enough friends for today” so we can leave.<br />
<br />
But then Pat remembers we have to take pictures and we’re in a parking lot behing Nexus X between two dumpsters. So I head to a wall where a huge girl in leggings is painted and head straight for the nipple, picking it between my fingers with a dumb smile while Pat goes for a muff dive.<br />
<br />
At that point were mad tired and we haven’t begun to drive so we’re anxious to experience Pat’s unstoppable laugher once again. We finally decide to stop at Napanee (home of Avril Lavigne if you want to know) at Pizza Hut and I think that is when the lack of sleep really hit.<br />
<br />
Me and Pat keep arguing about the toppings for the salad, for the pizza and Pat takes literally 2 minutes with the waiter waiting to decide between brisk iced tea or lemonade. When our meal finally arrives we’re already drunk on coke. At one point the radio plays some shimmerty dance music and we all start to nod our heads until my brother and I start dancing in the middle Pizza hut, him moving his arms and me slapping my ass.<br />
<br />
So the waitress comes back apparently not pleased with our dancing talents and it takes forever for the check to come. So Steve and my brother wait for me and Pat outside and we go to pay at the counter but have to wait for the machine to process his card. So meanwhile Pat sees a picture of a young man on the wall and thinks he’s the employee of the month and tells me really loud in front of the waitress: “ see Pat if you keep working hard you might become like him” so I look at the picture closer and it says “ in loving memory …”, so I immediately feel completely ackward while the waitress looks at Pat with angry eyes and I tell Pat the dude’s dead. If you have never seen Pat embarrassed, I strongly suggest you try it, It is a golden moment. Pat practically crawls out of the Pizza out we go back to the car.<br />
<br />
Steve takes over the drive and we all sleep while he listens to shimmerty dance music in order to keep him awake. We finally arrive in Montreal at 3:00 am after a 22 hours day preceded by a 1 hour and a half sleep. I was so tired I think I didn’t finish my sentence when I told my brother I was going to sleep.<br />
<br />
Props:<br />
-My brother for coming up with a real good deck idea of his own and being so close to making the bad beef final we have always dreamed of, maybe for the worlds… : ) Oh and also props to him for not yelling at anyone during a tournament.  : )<br />
-Pat for being the best road trip buddy ever, I so wish we win enough money to go to Amsterdam, it would be awesome.<br />
-Steve for being really nice and finishing 3-3 on his first ever big tournament. Way to go man, I hope we make many trips together in the future.<br />
-Nexus X for holding another great TOC.<br />
-Malcolm for being a really funny dwarf<br />
-Mike for being nice and for his great performance.<br />
-Pierre-Francois for playing a gollum-easterling deck at a TOC.<br />
-Steve for explaining to my bro how to trade and sell on internet.<br />
-The Toronto Maple Leafs for being the team with the most attitude.<br />
-The Anaheim Mighty Ducks for teaching Detroit a hockey lesson.<br />
-The girl in leggings behind Nexus-X<br />
-Avril Lavigne for surviving Napanee’s ugliness.<br />
-shimmerty dance music.<br />
<br />
Slops:<br />
-What did you expect? : JOSH<br />
-The new TOC binder (the old one was so cool).<br />
-No Heinz sauce at Pizza Hut<br />
-My gay stomach<br />
<br />
For those of you near Montreal, I invite you to the Montreal PSQ held at Quantum Cards on april 27th which I will be judging. For everyone else, I guess I’ll see you all in Origins. For Josh: Bite me.<br />
<br />
